This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and various cabinet members on the topic of healthcare and the opioid crisis. They discuss the implementation of the Mission Act, which provides greater choice in healthcare for veterans, and the success of the administration's efforts to combat the opioid crisis. They highlight the decrease in overdose deaths, the reduction in opioid prescriptions, and the seizure of drugs at the border. They also mention the importance of changing the culture around pain management and the need for non-addictive painkillers. The First Lady also speaks about her initiative, BE BEST, which aims to raise awareness about the dangers of drugs and reduce stigma around addiction. Overall, the remarks focus on the progress made in addressing the opioid crisis and the administration's ongoing efforts.